What Once Was

by Luke A. Jones
 (with some coding magic from K.V.)

You are in Your Office.

You can see Your Desk, Holly's Desk, a Computer, a Window, a Radiator and Your Desk Drawer.

You can go out.

You are in the cramped postgraduate office that you share with Holly, (who is currently away at a conference in the states). There are piles of journal papers everywhere and empty bottles of diet coke festoon your desk and the window sill. There are various posters and timetables blu-tacked to the walls.

You've just arrived at the office rather late after a heavy night's drinking at The Cross Keys with your housemate Phil, best check your email first and see what you've missed.

*****type 'hints' at any time for instructions and help******

> read email

> read email

You take a deep breath and steel yourself to deal with today's delivery of electronic mither and annoyance.

Amongst the usual academic spam and poorly directed mass emails from faculty, three emails from your supervisor marked 'URGENT' leap out of the screen at you.

Email sent today at 7:47am

"Where are you? It's nearly 8am, I had a breakthrough with the power problems we've been struggling with, meet me down at the lab when you finally get out of bed"

Email sent today at 8:33am

"OK I got bored waiting for you, I've implemented the power fix and the voltage seems to finally be stabilised. Come down to the lab and we'll try test run number 1337b. Also I've changed the  lab code, it's easy as 12,34,56,78"

Email sent today at 9:03am

"Right, I can't hang around all morning waiting for you, I have a damn programme committee meeting to attend at 9:30am, I'm going to do the trial run myself, I'll catch up with you later this afternoon when you finally crawl in"
